{"id":14881344,"mediaExerciseId":"a7b63c6b-7a6a-4c10-b18b-f33040ec36bd","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612362,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":415,"solutions":[{"id":6138900,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this question, we will try to disprove the age-old assumption that investing in stocks is the same as gambling. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Gambling, as defined in the dictionary, is the act of wagering an asset (usually money) in an event that has an uncertain outcome or an outcome that is purely determined by chance.\n\nFrom this definition alone, we know that investing in the stock market is not at all the same as gambling.\n\nFor one, when investing, there are a lot of markers and indicators that one can examine in order to predict the next possible outcome. Usually, the movement of the market is predictable, to some extent, by these factors. In gambling, no matter how much you analyze previous data, you cannot come as close to predicting the next outcome just as you would in the stock market. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Comparing the stock market with gambling is a misconception since investing also has its risks. However, investing involves analysis of data to make smart decisions while gambling essentially just relies on chance and probabilities that the gambler has no control over. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"753b5247-9796-41bd-ad62-0771e4cad40a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881345,"exerciseName":"9","page":415,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"070622ee-34cb-4c55-83cc-d43e371ff47d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-critical-thinking-questions-9-070622ee-34cb-4c55-83cc-d43e371ff47d"},{"id":14881346,"exerciseName":"10","page":415,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9c1de617-18c2-4f34-8635-f3cfce194027","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-critical-thinking-questions-10-9c1de617-18c2-4f34-8635-f3cfce194027"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881343,"exerciseName":"7","page":415,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ca9854a2-6ad4-4051-bb3e-2beb578d4ff7","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-critical-thinking-questions-7-ca9854a2-6ad4-4051-bb3e-2beb578d4ff7"},{"id":14881342,"exerciseName":"6","page":415,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"52145570-5363-468a-9bfb-fcd1d40dae12","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-critical-thinking-questions-6-52145570-5363-468a-9bfb-fcd1d40dae12"}],"